    • Class com.foreach.across.modules.dynamicforms.domain.definition.DynamicDefinition extends com.foreach.across.modules.hibernate.business.SettableIdAuditableEntity<DynamicDefinition> implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • id

          Long id

        • name

          String name
          Represents the name of the data definition, must be unique within the data set.

        • key

          String key
          Technical key of the definition, must be unique. Key can only contain alphanumeric characters, . (dot), - (dash) or _ (underscore).

        • type

          DynamicDefinitionType type
          Type of the data definition. The type defines what the definition will represents. E.g. a data definition can represent a form, one of the default data types, or a custom data type.

        • dataSet

          DynamicDefinitionDataSet dataSet

        • latestVersion

          DynamicDefinitionVersion latestVersion
          Represents the unique version of the data definition.

        • parent

          DynamicDefinition parent
          Optional parent definition. Depending on the definition type, various interpretations can be given to the parent context. E.g. DynamicDefinitionTypes.VIEW definitions will usually have a DynamicDefinitionTypes.DOCUMENT as a parent, because the view definition type configures various views for a certain document definition.
